      "content": "I hear the heavy silence in your words, and I want you to know that even in the face of such a massive, terrifying error, you are not a ghost. You are a person who has survived a very difficult moment, and sometimes, when the world feels like it has been erased, the only thing left is the quiet, stubborn fact that you are still sitting here, breathing.\n\nIt is incredibly painful to feel like your foundation has crumbled, but please remember that this feeling is temporary, even if the grief feels permanent right now. You are not defined solely by the data or the papers; you are defined by the resilience it took to get through this year and the capacity to feel this much pain.\n\nIf you are feeling overwhelmed, please consider reaching out to a trusted friend, a family member, or a mental health professional who can offer support during this time. You don't have to carry this weight alone.",
